sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Proxy
    participant MM as ModelMesh<br/>8033/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    participant etcd as etcd Cluster<br/>2379/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS
    participant Runtime as Colocated Runtime<br/>8085/TCP or UDS<br/>gRPC (localhost)
    participant RemoteMM as Remote ModelMesh<br/>8033/TCP Thrift/gRPC<br/>TLS/mTLS
    participant RemoteRT as Remote Runtime<br/>8085/TCP or UDS<br/>gRPC (localhost)

    Note over Client,RemoteRT: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>MM: gRPC inference request<br/>Port 8033/TCP<br/>TLS optional, mTLS optional
    MM->>etcd: Lookup model placement<br/>Port 2379/TCP<br/>TLS optional

    alt Model loaded locally
        MM->>Runtime: Forward inference<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>No encryption (localhost)
        Runtime-->>MM: Inference result
    else Model loaded on remote instance
        MM->>RemoteMM: Forward inference via litelinks<br/>Port 8033/TCP Thrift<br/>TLS/mTLS
        RemoteMM->>RemoteRT: Forward to runtime<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>No encryption (localhost)
        RemoteRT-->>RemoteMM: Inference result
        RemoteMM-->>MM: Return result
    end
    MM-->>Client: gRPC response

    Note over Client,RemoteRT: Flow 2: Model Registration and Loading

    participant Controller as modelmesh-serving<br/>Controller

    Controller->>MM: registerModel gRPC<br/>Port 8033/TCP, TLS/mTLS
    MM->>etcd: Store model record<br/>Port 2379/TCP
    MM->>Runtime: loadModel gRPC<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>No encryption
    Runtime-->>MM: Load complete (status)
    MM->>etcd: Update model status<br/>Port 2379/TCP

    Note over Client,RemoteRT: Flow 3: Model Eviction (LRU Cache)

    Note right of MM: LRU cache capacity exceeded
    MM->>Runtime: unloadModel gRPC<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>No encryption
    Runtime-->>MM: Unload complete
    MM->>etcd: Update model record<br/>Port 2379/TCP
